From d789b1467c84580f18fec9f97818f3974aae3d3a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Olav Tvete <paul.tvete@qt.io>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 17:52:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] [Wayland] Give focus to embedded windows

The Wayland specification was changed to specify that sub-surfaces
should no longer receive keyboard focus. Since Qt assumes that all
windows will get focus/activation, we have to emulate that in the
platform plugin. This change gives the active focus to a window
with a sub-surface if it is pressed while its toplevel surface
is active.

Fixes: QTBUG-123455
Change-Id: Ib1770e54f43b2d14b88d21bb8babf86b2a300b5e
Reviewed-by: David Edmundson <davidedmundson@kde.org>
